  /*
    ## Chalk Colors and Styles

    ### Basic Colors
    - black
    - red
    - green
    - yellow
    - blue
    - magenta
    - cyan
    - white

    ### Bright Colors
    - blackBright (alias: gray, grey)
    - redBright
    - greenBright
    - yellowBright
    - blueBright
    - magentaBright
    - cyanBright
    - whiteBright

    ### Background Colors
    - bgBlack
    - bgRed
    - bgGreen
    - bgYellow
    - bgBlue
    - bgMagenta
    - bgCyan
    - bgWhite

    ### Bright Background Colors
    - bgBlackBright (alias: bgGray, bgGrey)
    - bgRedBright
    - bgGreenBright
    - bgYellowBright
    - bgBlueBright
    - bgMagentaBright
    - bgCyanBright
    - bgWhiteBright

    ### Modifiers
    - reset: Reset the current style.
    - bold: Make the text bold.
    - dim: Make the text have lower opacity.
    - italic: Make the text italic (not widely supported).
    - underline: Underline the text.
    - overline: Overline the text (not widely supported).
    - inverse: Invert background and foreground colors.
    - hidden: Make the text invisible.
    - strikethrough: Strikethrough the text (not widely supported).
    - visible: Print the text only when Chalk has a color level above zero.

    ### Advanced Color Support
    - RGB Colors: chalk.rgb(r, g, b)
    - Hex Colors: chalk.hex('#RRGGBB')
    - 256 Colors: chalk.ansi256(n)

    ### Usage Example
    import chalk from 'chalk';

    console.log(chalk.red('This is red text'));
    console.log(chalk.greenBright('This is bright green text'));
    console.log(chalk.bgBlue('This text has a blue background'));
    console.log(chalk.bold.underline('This text is bold and underlined'));
    console.log(chalk.rgb(123, 45, 67).underline('Underlined reddish color'));
    console.log(chalk.hex('#DEADED').bold('Bold gray!'));

    ### Additional Resources
    For more details, visit the Chalk GitHub repository: https://github.com/chalk/chalk
  */
    